1
00:00:00,929 --> 00:00:05,160
I've been doing my best!
I've been trying so hard!

2
00:00:05,903 --> 00:00:09,440
But couldn't you be a little kinder to him?

3
00:00:10,216 --> 00:00:12,156
This family is seriously messed up.

4
00:00:12,630 --> 00:00:13,840
Let go of me!

5
00:00:16,004 --> 00:00:19,293
Because you're you, Chika.

6
00:00:19,596 --> 00:00:24,720
Um, I... It's love. Love.

7
00:00:26,076 --> 00:00:27,840
Um, probably.

8
00:00:28,663 --> 00:00:30,043
Get results.

9
00:00:30,995 --> 00:00:33,360
- Huh?
- Don't "huh" me.

10
00:00:33,823 --> 00:00:36,800
The only way to show it to that woman is
for you to get results.

11
00:00:37,863 --> 00:00:40,240
Results? Like what?

12
00:00:40,603 --> 00:00:44,663
Uh, I mean, if you're saying I should become
a big-shot writer or something...

13
00:00:44,890 --> 00:00:47,720
Shut up. Scram! Shoo!

14
00:00:54,955 --> 00:00:56,716
No, but, like...

15
00:00:58,170 --> 00:01:02,680
Results aren't really something
you can get overnight, you know.

16
00:01:05,573 --> 00:01:06,960
But I'll try.

17
00:01:09,391 --> 00:01:13,120
With the Ichimotsu Dance,
every girl near and far...

18
00:01:13,217 --> 00:01:17,996
Won't you come
and do it, do it, do it with me?

19
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:19,407
One more time!

20
00:01:19,447 --> 00:01:23,680
Here we go! With the Ichimotsu Dance,
every girl near and far...

21
00:01:23,687 --> 00:01:28,447
Won't you come
and do it, do it, do it with me?

22
00:01:28,487 --> 00:01:30,560
What a funny song!

23
00:01:30,753 --> 00:01:33,893
Maybe don't sing it around the girls, though.

24
00:01:34,028 --> 00:01:39,506
Taro, you're so good! I'd love
to hear some other ones, too!

25
00:01:39,546 --> 00:01:40,601
Well, if you insist.

26
00:01:40,641 --> 00:01:42,679
I'll teach you another one next time.

27
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:43,773
Oh, what song?

28
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:44,813
"Egotism."

29
00:01:44,846 --> 00:01:46,320
Oh, "Egotism?"

30
00:01:46,428 --> 00:01:48,113
- See you next time!
- Goodbye!

31
00:01:48,153 --> 00:01:49,197
Bye-bye!

32
00:01:49,237 --> 00:01:51,480
- Goodbye.
- Be safe! See you, Taro!

33
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:57,040
Taro was livelier than he had
ever been before in this class.

34
00:01:57,240 --> 00:02:00,880
He was pouting about only getting
two hours of iPad a day, though.

35
00:02:01,108 --> 00:02:03,119
Yeah, he's been doing great lately.

36
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:05,260
He's gone to school three days in a row now.

37
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:07,600
Wow, Taro, you're really hanging in there!

38
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,960
I'm not hanging in there.

39
00:02:10,692 --> 00:02:16,240
Same as when he makes it to school,
please praise him a lot when he sings.

40
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:22,520
That builds confidence and helps him grow
his self-esteem bit by bit.

41
00:02:23,260 --> 00:02:24,880
Small steps.

42
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,600
Small steps.

43
00:02:27,286 --> 00:02:29,600
Having something you love is
a wonderful thing.

44
00:02:31,646 --> 00:02:33,280
Thank you.

45
00:02:33,999 --> 00:02:36,720
Bye now, Taro.
Teach me more Doburock next time!

46
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,000
Sure!

47
00:02:38,058 --> 00:02:40,000
- Goodbye.
- Take care!

48
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:42,441
Teach me more Doburock, okay?

49
00:02:42,481 --> 00:02:43,673
Yeah, sure!

50
00:02:43,713 --> 00:02:44,913
Bye-bye!

51
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:52,480
When you skip school, when you skip school...

52
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,892
Oh, nice one, Taro!

53
00:02:56,018 --> 00:02:57,251
Right?

54
00:02:59,501 --> 00:03:01,120
I'm home.

55
00:03:02,215 --> 00:03:04,138
Welcome back-apple!

56
00:03:04,178 --> 00:03:06,761
I'm home-melon!

57
00:03:06,801 --> 00:03:11,040
So today, the teacher at Sunflower said
that Doburock's songs are funny!

58
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,040
"Ichimotsu Dance" and "Egotism."

59
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:15,846
Mom, you haven't heard "Egotism" yet, right?
Listen to it!

60
00:03:15,886 --> 00:03:17,120
Oh, okay, okay!

61
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,721
Just a sec, let me go change first.

62
00:03:18,761 --> 00:03:20,100
Okay. Come right back after that!

63
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:21,800
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

64
00:03:24,093 --> 00:03:25,360
Welcome back.

65
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:27,240
Oh, you're here.

66
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:29,120
I am.

67
00:03:37,130 --> 00:03:42,480
Ever since Chika told me to produce results,
she hasn't brought it up again.

68
00:03:42,946 --> 00:03:48,400
I was hoping that maybe she had
forgotten about it or forgiven me, but...

69
00:03:52,497 --> 00:03:54,640
Why are you here? You're so damn in the way.

70
00:03:55,097 --> 00:03:57,880
I wanted to share
what happened at Sunflower today.

71
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:01,841
Taro has been singing Doburock songs nonstop.

72
00:04:01,881 --> 00:04:05,840
The teacher said we should keep praising him
for stuff like that, to build his confidence.

73
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:10,280
She said that building up
his self-esteem is what really matters.

74
00:04:10,469 --> 00:04:15,000
I've been saying that forever!
It's your fault.

75
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:20,870
Nagging him to watch other videos or Ghibli.
Just hurry up and get results already.

76
00:04:20,910 --> 00:04:22,767
Hey, stop fighting already.

77
00:04:22,807 --> 00:04:26,268
Yeah. Sorry,
Daddy started saying weird stuff again.

78
00:04:26,308 --> 00:04:28,481
Oh, let me see! Doburock's new song?

79
00:04:32,729 --> 00:04:35,360
As I suspected, I had not been forgiven.

80
00:04:45,119 --> 00:04:47,246
Alright!

81
00:04:50,313 --> 00:04:51,513
Ta-da!

82
00:04:52,226 --> 00:04:53,766
Yay!

83
00:04:53,946 --> 00:04:55,380
Thank you!

84
00:04:58,393 --> 00:04:59,593
Here we go!

85
00:05:07,412 --> 00:05:10,266
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

86
00:05:36,932 --> 00:05:39,786
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

87
00:05:40,459 --> 00:05:43,094
Episode 9: There Are Times
When You Must Get Results

88
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:47,280
What does she mean by "get results?"
You already did, didn't you?

89
00:05:47,395 --> 00:05:48,950
What do you mean?

90
00:05:48,990 --> 00:05:52,970
I mean, this
is
the result, isn't it?
What more results could there be?

91
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:54,850
Hey, that's harsh.

92
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:58,850
But honestly, Gota would be
a no for me too. Sorry.

93
00:05:58,988 --> 00:06:02,536
A man with no income...
That's a deal-breaker.

94
00:06:03,916 --> 00:06:05,913
This is not the time to laugh.

95
00:06:06,689 --> 00:06:08,600
All I can do is laugh.

96
00:06:08,611 --> 00:06:14,415
I mean, my line of work isn't the kind
where you get results overnight.

97
00:06:14,455 --> 00:06:17,120
That's dumb. Every job is like that.

98
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:18,570
- So true.
- Right?

99
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:22,633
But you wouldn't tell someone to get results
unless you actually cared, would you?

100
00:06:22,673 --> 00:06:24,710
You wouldn't say that
if you didn't give a damn.

101
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:26,720
- That's true.
- Good point.

102
00:06:26,809 --> 00:06:30,953
If this happened to me, I'd cut ties
with the husband and his mom.

103
00:06:31,615 --> 00:06:34,250
That's why Chika is
kinda an idiot too, in a way.

104
00:06:34,290 --> 00:06:38,360
At this point, she's still telling him
to get results? Still expecting something?

105
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:42,410
She kinda wants to prove
my mom wrong, I think.

106
00:06:42,450 --> 00:06:47,520
Oh, I get that. Mothers-in-law have it easy.
They only raise them until they're twenty.

107
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:50,863
- True.
- We have to put up with them for life.

108
00:06:50,903 --> 00:06:52,720
Exactly!

109
00:06:53,176 --> 00:06:55,076
Guess you gotta get results.

110
00:06:55,116 --> 00:06:56,356
Yeah.

111
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:59,330
But what if I can't get results...

112
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:04,800
You have no choice! There are times
when you must get results.

113
00:07:05,195 --> 00:07:06,428
Right?

114
00:07:06,454 --> 00:07:08,500
- Right! It's true.
- Totally.

115
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:11,173
- Totally!
- Totally!

116
00:07:14,944 --> 00:07:18,640
Wait. But what if I still can't get results?

117
00:07:19,329 --> 00:07:20,920
Then you might as well die.

118
00:07:21,870 --> 00:07:23,840
Wait, die?!

119
00:07:24,263 --> 00:07:27,320
I mean, I've got nothing to lose either.
I decided to get divorced.

120
00:07:27,963 --> 00:07:33,589
I used to think dating apps were gross,
but when you're desperate, you just do it.

121
00:07:34,149 --> 00:07:38,240
And now I'm like,
why didn't I do this sooner?

122
00:07:39,056 --> 00:07:40,947
I got a boyfriend right away.

123
00:07:40,987 --> 00:07:42,256
What?!

124
00:07:42,262 --> 00:07:43,482
That guy.

125
00:07:44,375 --> 00:07:46,280
Wait, he is your boyfriend?!

126
00:07:46,369 --> 00:07:48,215
Uh, he's not cute at all though.

127
00:07:48,255 --> 00:07:52,920
What are you saying? It's not about looks.
It's personality. Personality!

128
00:07:53,303 --> 00:07:55,760
We're practically living together now.

129
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:57,316
- What?!
- Seriously?

130
00:07:57,356 --> 00:07:58,426
What about Mina?

131
00:07:58,466 --> 00:08:04,520
She totally loves him. He's closer in age
than my ex, and he plays with her a lot.

132
00:08:05,802 --> 00:08:09,880
We're doing it every day,
so I'm super happy right now.

133
00:08:10,476 --> 00:08:16,400
If you're happy, fine, but be careful.
You just met him, so you don't know him yet.

134
00:08:16,588 --> 00:08:18,569
The fact that he came here is a red flag.

135
00:08:18,609 --> 00:08:20,061
- It's fine.
- Sketchy.

136
00:08:20,101 --> 00:08:21,955
It's dangerous. So dangerous.

137
00:08:21,995 --> 00:08:24,480
If he tries anything weird,
I'll kick him out.

138
00:08:25,961 --> 00:08:28,927
Why didn't I do this sooner?

139
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:32,222
You guys should all try dating apps, too.

140
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:33,647
What? Why?

141
00:08:33,687 --> 00:08:37,080
Why not? If you're gonna complain
about your husbands, just move on.

142
00:08:37,236 --> 00:08:40,909
Life's short. Live for yourself.

143
00:08:41,463 --> 00:08:44,121
You're not living
for your kids or your husband.

144
00:08:44,161 --> 00:08:46,632
Sure, they can be part of the fun,

145
00:08:46,672 --> 00:08:50,160
but if you don't put yourself first,
what's the point of living?

146
00:08:51,678 --> 00:08:52,710
"Yourself first?"

147
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:57,350
So Gota, you better get real results,
or Chika might go "me first" on you.

148
00:08:57,390 --> 00:08:59,363
- Are you Yuriko Koike?
- Chika might think that.

149
00:08:59,403 --> 00:09:00,403
Yuriko! Yuriko!

150
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:01,760
"First! First!"

151
00:09:01,826 --> 00:09:03,026
Right...

152
00:09:03,970 --> 00:09:07,970
What's that reaction? That's exactly
why Chika gets so frustrated with you.

153
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:09,295
Exactly.

154
00:09:09,335 --> 00:09:10,794
That dopey face is gross.

155
00:09:10,834 --> 00:09:11,901
It gives me the chills.

156
00:09:11,941 --> 00:09:13,390
Why do you always laugh?

157
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:15,249
Stop it, seriously.

158
00:09:15,289 --> 00:09:17,799
- Close your mouth.
- Stop it already.

159
00:09:18,007 --> 00:09:19,701
I'm about to lose it.

160
00:09:23,349 --> 00:09:27,600
It's amazing, Taro.
You've been going to school lately.

161
00:09:28,182 --> 00:09:29,560
Is school fun?

162
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:36,640
Well... not really, but kinda fun, I guess.

163
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:41,030
But hey, since I'm going to school,
can I join the Doburock fan club?

164
00:09:41,070 --> 00:09:43,760
Once you can go every day.

165
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:51,240
You're so greedy, Dad.

166
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,920
Yes, I am.

167
00:09:54,082 --> 00:09:56,135
- Could it be...
- Could it be...

168
00:09:56,175 --> 00:09:58,321
- Could it be...
- Could it be...

169
00:09:58,361 --> 00:10:00,343
That you are...

170
00:10:00,383 --> 00:10:02,555
- Trying to hit on me?
- Trying to hit on me?

171
00:10:02,618 --> 00:10:05,726
A girl at the convenience store...

172
00:10:05,766 --> 00:10:07,390
I don't know this part...

173
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:11,136
Held out her hand to me, asking for change,

174
00:10:12,043 --> 00:10:15,808
and made me count it out.

175
00:10:15,848 --> 00:10:17,809
- Could it be...
- Could it be...

176
00:10:17,849 --> 00:10:19,522
- Could it be...
- Could it be...

177
00:10:19,562 --> 00:10:21,800
That you are...

178
00:10:23,535 --> 00:10:24,535
We're home!

179
00:10:24,536 --> 00:10:25,840
We're back.

180
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,680
- Hey, welcome home!
- Oh, you were home?

181
00:10:28,966 --> 00:10:30,902
You should've come to the community kitchen!

182
00:10:30,942 --> 00:10:31,976
I just got back.

183
00:10:32,016 --> 00:10:34,338
So Taro, what did you eat? Was it good?

184
00:10:34,356 --> 00:10:35,776
The fried chicken was great, right?

185
00:10:35,816 --> 00:10:37,600
I wasn't asking you.

186
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:39,043
The fried chicken was yummy.

187
00:10:39,083 --> 00:10:40,390
Hmm, can I use the iPad?

188
00:10:40,430 --> 00:10:41,790
Only when your homework's done.

189
00:10:41,830 --> 00:10:43,036
Hm?

190
00:10:43,506 --> 00:10:45,720
Oh, he did it at the community kitchen.

191
00:10:45,816 --> 00:10:49,750
I said I'm not asking you!
Let Taro answer for himself.

192
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:51,120
I did it!

193
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:52,875
- Right?
- Huh?

194
00:10:52,915 --> 00:10:57,800
Taro, I told you to give
this handout to your teacher!

195
00:10:57,982 --> 00:11:00,101
Why didn't you hand it in?

196
00:11:01,009 --> 00:11:05,760
Wait, Taro, what's this?
"Comedy committee member."

197
00:11:06,069 --> 00:11:07,609
Taro, you got picked for this?

198
00:11:09,174 --> 00:11:11,216
Yeah, I kinda was.

199
00:11:11,256 --> 00:11:13,737
- What?!
- What's the "comedy committee?"

200
00:11:13,777 --> 00:11:16,810
That's amazing! Wow, it's so cool!

201
00:11:16,850 --> 00:11:19,040
And you volunteered for it?

202
00:11:19,176 --> 00:11:22,373
I'm so proud of you, Taro.

203
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,760
What does the comedy committee do?

204
00:11:24,830 --> 00:11:27,345
Hey, enough already. Just praise him first.

205
00:11:27,385 --> 00:11:30,455
Taro has never volunteered
for any role before.

206
00:11:30,489 --> 00:11:32,360
Did you even check the contact notebook?

207
00:11:32,569 --> 00:11:35,723
Taro, don't you think that being
in the comedy committee is perfect for you?

208
00:11:35,763 --> 00:11:38,443
I was beyond happy about Taro's progress,

209
00:11:38,856 --> 00:11:44,040
but thinking about my own need
to get results cut my joy in half.

210
00:11:44,223 --> 00:11:46,561
Maybe I'm just a lousy father.

211
00:11:46,601 --> 00:11:48,000
Taro!

212
00:11:48,956 --> 00:11:50,163
It's so cool!

213
00:11:54,326 --> 00:11:59,000
I was surprised. He had always refused
to take on any class role before.

214
00:11:59,019 --> 00:12:04,600
Taro seems to love Doburock.
He often sings their songs at school.

215
00:12:05,660 --> 00:12:07,960
There are four kids in the comedy committee.

216
00:12:08,055 --> 00:12:12,200
They share fun or funny things
that happened that day.

217
00:12:12,446 --> 00:12:16,320
Taro talks about it with such joy.
It's wonderful.

218
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:20,720
This could be a stepping stone
for him to build relationships.

219
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:23,680
But I'd like us to take it slow
and not rush things.

220
00:12:24,104 --> 00:12:26,466
Thank you so much.
Please keep looking after him.

221
00:12:26,506 --> 00:12:29,789
Lately at home too, he seems
a bit happier, don't you think?

222
00:12:29,829 --> 00:12:34,800
But times like this are when I want
to push too hard, so I'll watch myself.

223
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:38,880
Yes. I know I said not to rush,

224
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:44,815
but at the next school assembly,
the comedy committee is performing something.

225
00:12:45,196 --> 00:12:46,196
Taro, too.

226
00:12:46,226 --> 00:12:48,864
- What?
- Taro's performing, too?

227
00:12:48,904 --> 00:12:52,792
Hey, keep your voice down.
Did he volunteer for this himself?

228
00:12:53,086 --> 00:12:58,167
He's pretty enthusiastic so far,
but I'm sure there'll be some trouble

229
00:12:58,207 --> 00:13:01,200
about what kind of act to do
and things like that.

230
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:03,579
So, I'll keep an eye on how it goes.

231
00:13:03,619 --> 00:13:06,845
Can he really handle it?

232
00:13:06,885 --> 00:13:12,160
Like I said before,
he gets extremely anxious with new things.

233
00:13:12,232 --> 00:13:18,213
In preschool too, he flat-out refused
to join the field day and the school play.

234
00:13:18,253 --> 00:13:21,313
That's why I said don't panic.
He always freaks out like this.

235
00:13:21,353 --> 00:13:27,950
But what if it doesn't go well
and he ends up hating school again?

236
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:30,596
Hey, nothing's even happened yet.

237
00:13:30,636 --> 00:13:33,850
When is this school assembly?

238
00:13:34,179 --> 00:13:39,058
It's next Monday, so very soon.
I'll be keeping a close watch on him, too.

239
00:13:39,098 --> 00:13:41,466
Even if Taro can't go through
with it at the last minute,

240
00:13:41,506 --> 00:13:45,790
we can just look the other way
and smoothly move things along.

241
00:13:46,153 --> 00:13:47,719
Thank you. We appreciate it.

242
00:13:47,759 --> 00:13:52,925
Next Monday? That's so soon.
What's he gonna do for material?

243
00:13:52,965 --> 00:13:54,300
You're the one I'm worried about.

244
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:56,260
Well, it's that kind of work, you know...

245
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,610
Shut up, you're unemployed.

246
00:13:57,650 --> 00:14:00,700
No, not right now... I have a job now.

247
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:03,253
Why are you showing off
in front of the teacher? So gross.

248
00:14:03,293 --> 00:14:04,673
Sorry about him.

249
00:14:04,713 --> 00:14:07,160
It's not 'cause the teacher's here
or anything like that.

250
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,826
I see you two are as close as ever.

251
00:14:08,866 --> 00:14:11,400
We're not close at all. We're at rock bottom.

252
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,856
- Rock bottom?
- Barely hanging on.

253
00:14:12,896 --> 00:14:15,375
- Barely...?
- It's not "barely!" We get along fine.

254
00:14:15,415 --> 00:14:17,467
We do not. Sorry about this, really.

255
00:14:17,507 --> 00:14:19,246
You really are close, aren't you?

256
00:14:23,380 --> 00:14:24,601
We're home.

257
00:14:24,641 --> 00:14:27,680
We're home, Taro.

258
00:14:27,853 --> 00:14:34,432
Taro, your teacher told us!
You're performing on Monday? That's amazing!

259
00:14:34,472 --> 00:14:35,880
Do you want Papa to help you?

260
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:38,117
That's exactly the kind of pressure
I told you about!

261
00:14:38,157 --> 00:14:41,897
Stop getting ahead of yourself.
Just tell Taro he's amazing. That's enough.

262
00:14:41,937 --> 00:14:47,495
I know, but I worry a little.
It's because I care so much about him.

263
00:14:47,535 --> 00:14:52,450
Wow, that self-esteem of yours.
No surprise, raised by that mother.

264
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:54,479
Hey, stop fighting!

265
00:14:54,519 --> 00:14:57,680
You see, cut it out already.
He's sensitive to loud noises!

266
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,033
But Chika, you started...

267
00:14:59,073 --> 00:15:01,840
I said stop. Do you not understand Japanese?

268
00:15:02,079 --> 00:15:05,160
Then Papa, write me some material.
I wanna practice together.

269
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:09,480
See? Okay, Taro, let's do it.
I'll write something!

270
00:15:10,019 --> 00:15:11,291
Mama, you're doing it, too.

271
00:15:11,331 --> 00:15:13,253
Huh? I'm good, thanks.

272
00:15:13,293 --> 00:15:15,640
Just do it.

273
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:21,108
Okay! Papa will write something funny
which we can practice together!

274
00:15:21,269 --> 00:15:25,505
You know, Papa actually wanted
to be a comedian once.

275
00:15:25,545 --> 00:15:27,040
- Right?
- How should I know?

276
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:30,161
Come on, we used to go
to comedy shows together all the time.

277
00:15:30,201 --> 00:15:32,600
You even said I was funnier
than the comedians, Chika.

278
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:33,960
I would never say that.

279
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:38,400
Enough fighting. Just hurry up and write it.
Make it funnier than Doburock!

280
00:15:38,446 --> 00:15:44,532
Okay. Then handle dinner tonight, please.
There's pork, so just make whatever.

281
00:15:44,572 --> 00:15:45,772
Yeah.

282
00:15:48,703 --> 00:15:50,560
It's gonna be boring if Papa writes it.

283
00:15:52,111 --> 00:15:53,500
That's why you should help, too.

284
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:56,480
If I did, it'd end up way too funny.

285
00:16:18,026 --> 00:16:23,480
I spent thirty minutes seriously thinking,
but couldn't come up with anything.

286
00:16:23,959 --> 00:16:28,280
But it's just elementary kids performing
for other elementary kids.

287
00:16:28,539 --> 00:16:30,800
I could just throw something together.

288
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:36,800
And best of all, this could be
my chance to make up with Chika.

289
00:16:47,942 --> 00:16:49,600
Yeah, that's right.

290
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:55,520
He just wants us to get along.

291
00:17:11,815 --> 00:17:15,550
Taro, ready? Raise or lower the flags
when Papa tells you, okay?

292
00:17:15,590 --> 00:17:17,810
- Got it.
- Okay, loser gets a penalty!

293
00:17:17,850 --> 00:17:18,922
Huh? What?

294
00:17:18,962 --> 00:17:20,516
- What's the penalty?
- Funny face.

295
00:17:20,556 --> 00:17:22,290
- Funny face!
- Oh, come on.

296
00:17:22,330 --> 00:17:24,330
- Okay, here we go! Ready?
- So old-school.

297
00:17:24,370 --> 00:17:26,680
Ready, go! Raise red!

298
00:17:27,110 --> 00:17:28,480
Raise white!

299
00:17:28,843 --> 00:17:31,680
Don't lower red! Lower white!

300
00:17:32,523 --> 00:17:33,840
Lower red!

301
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:35,520
Raise red!

302
00:17:35,677 --> 00:17:37,487
Don't lower white.

303
00:17:37,623 --> 00:17:38,650
Raise red!

304
00:17:38,690 --> 00:17:42,095
Wait, what? I don't get it anymore!

305
00:17:42,135 --> 00:17:43,768
Time for your funny face!

306
00:17:43,808 --> 00:17:46,636
- Funny face! Funny face!
- Funny face! Funny face!

307
00:17:48,789 --> 00:17:49,948
What is wrong with you?

308
00:17:49,988 --> 00:17:51,310
- Again, one more time!
- Again!

309
00:17:51,350 --> 00:17:52,640
Again?!

310
00:17:52,703 --> 00:17:54,920
Ready, go! Raise red!

311
00:17:54,929 --> 00:17:56,320
Raise white!

312
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:59,889
Don't lower red! Lower white!

313
00:17:59,929 --> 00:18:01,750
Wait, hold on...

314
00:18:01,868 --> 00:18:03,770
- You set the pace wrong!
- No, no, no!

315
00:18:03,810 --> 00:18:05,230
The pace was good.

316
00:18:05,270 --> 00:18:08,440
- Funny face. Funny face.
- Funny face. Funny face.

317
00:18:08,623 --> 00:18:09,921
Here we go.

318
00:18:10,956 --> 00:18:12,163
First time seeing that.

319
00:18:12,203 --> 00:18:15,043
What do you mean by "first time?"
This was my first time doing it!

320
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:17,556
- One more time?
- Isn't it enough?

321
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,510
One more! One more!

322
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:23,802
Okay, Taro, did you get it?
Just do it the same way as Papa did it.

323
00:18:23,842 --> 00:18:24,901
Okay, I got it!

324
00:18:24,941 --> 00:18:26,930
- Just say whatever.
- Why do I have to do this?

325
00:18:26,970 --> 00:18:28,336
Here I go, Mama. Ready?

326
00:18:28,376 --> 00:18:30,160
Ugh, fine. Go ahead.

327
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:34,400
Raise red. Raise white.

328
00:18:35,010 --> 00:18:38,160
Don't lower white, don't lower red.

329
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:41,150
- Wait, what?
- They were both "Don't lower."

330
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:42,716
Funny face.

331
00:18:43,228 --> 00:18:44,690
I lost the last round, too!

332
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:45,761
- Funny face.
- Funny face.

333
00:18:45,801 --> 00:18:47,080
Okay, here we go.

334
00:18:48,599 --> 00:18:52,625
How long has it been
since our family laughed together like this?

335
00:18:52,665 --> 00:18:55,670
Seriously, what even is this?
It's not even a real comedy bit.

336
00:18:55,710 --> 00:18:59,228
No, this kind of thing is great.
Look, everyone's cracking up.

337
00:18:59,268 --> 00:19:02,040
- Yeah!
- Plus, it's got funny faces in it.

338
00:19:02,130 --> 00:19:03,950
Only you and Taro are laughing!

339
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:05,730
That's not true, right, Taro?

340
00:19:05,770 --> 00:19:07,115
- One more time!
- One more!

341
00:19:07,155 --> 00:19:09,190
Wait, hold on. This really is the last one!

342
00:19:09,230 --> 00:19:10,852
- OK. Last one, got it?
- Yeah, last one.

343
00:19:10,892 --> 00:19:12,264
Okay, fine.

344
00:19:13,329 --> 00:19:14,880
Raise white...

345
00:19:15,555 --> 00:19:16,587
Hey, wait a sec!

346
00:19:16,627 --> 00:19:18,447
- You missed the very first one!
- Hold on!

347
00:19:18,487 --> 00:19:20,289
- Funny face.
- Let's make this white, too.

348
00:19:20,329 --> 00:19:22,548
- Funny face!
- Funny face!

349
00:19:22,588 --> 00:19:24,680
Got it. Okay, what should I do?

350
00:19:25,241 --> 00:19:27,560
- I don't know.
- She's getting sloppy, right?

351
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:30,258
Did you just say "sloppy?"
Want me to kill you?

352
00:19:30,334 --> 00:19:32,007
Don't mess with me, seriously.

353
00:20:10,563 --> 00:20:11,789
Hey, um...

354
00:20:11,829 --> 00:20:13,320
Hm? What?

355
00:20:14,222 --> 00:20:15,520
You know,

356
00:20:16,470 --> 00:20:19,360
Taro has changed a bit, hasn't he?

357
00:20:19,675 --> 00:20:24,120
Yeah, I guess. He never used to laugh
that hard before.

358
00:20:28,233 --> 00:20:31,607
Honestly, more than getting results myself...

359
00:20:32,766 --> 00:20:35,840
Taro's growth makes me way happier.

360
00:20:36,673 --> 00:20:41,193
Huh? Are you trying to weasel out
of getting results?

361
00:20:41,379 --> 00:20:45,280
You only think of yourself!
Shut up and go get some results already.

362
00:20:47,446 --> 00:20:48,677
You sure?

363
00:20:50,786 --> 00:20:52,726
Obviously.

364
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:56,480
Just so we're clear,
this is not about whether we do it or not.

365
00:20:56,959 --> 00:21:00,720
If you don't deliver results, I don’t know
what will happen to our marriage.

366
00:21:33,670 --> 00:21:35,750
Hey, don't turn on the light!

367
00:21:35,790 --> 00:21:37,120
I didn't...

368
00:21:53,615 --> 00:21:55,240
Shut up, baldy.

369
00:21:55,620 --> 00:21:57,920
Wait, you are not bald.

370
00:21:59,535 --> 00:22:00,760
Sorry.

371
00:22:03,332 --> 00:22:07,240
I just had a brilliant idea.

372
00:22:14,650 --> 00:22:15,650
Next Episode Preview

373
00:22:15,683 --> 00:22:18,300
Wanna form a comedy duo with me?

374
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:21,207
Why the hell would I be your comedy partner?

375
00:22:21,247 --> 00:22:24,880
I just feel like it'd totally work
if I teamed up with you, Chika.

376
00:22:24,993 --> 00:22:26,466
Fine, I'll do it then.

377
00:22:26,506 --> 00:22:27,521
Don't bail on me.

378
00:22:27,561 --> 00:22:29,600
I won't...
